# Forensic Tool Capability Extension — Exemplar Instances (A-Box) v0.3.0
#
# This file contains validated example instances of the toolcap extension
# classes, demonstrating how to model forensic tool capabilities, benchmark
# observations, platform specifications, and access restrictions.
#
# The scenario models two commercial DFIR tools (Tool A and Tool B) and their
# ability to parse two applications: a messaging app (App Alpha) and an email
# client (Outlook). Outlook has two data format versions (.pst and .nst) to
# demonstrate how the extension tracks format-level capability gaps and
# benchmark observations over time.
#
# v0.3.0 adds NIST CFTT-style task-level capabilities (file carving, deleted
# file recovery, string search) with AutoDFBench IR metrics (precision,
# recall, F1, TP, FP, FN), benchmark provenance, and filesystem-aware
# platform specifications.
#
# Validation command:
#   case_validate --built-version case-1.4.0 \
#     --ontology-graph extensions/toolcap/toolcap.ttl \
#     --ontology-graph extensions/toolcap/toolcap-shapes.ttl \
#     --inference rdfs --allow-info \
#     extensions/toolcap/toolcap-exemplar.ttl

@prefix kb: <http://example.org/kb/> .
@prefix toolcap: <http://example.org/ontology/toolcap/> .
@prefix uco-core: <https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/core/> .
@prefix uco-tool: <https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/tool/> .
@prefix uco-identity: <https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/identity/> .
@prefix uco-observable: <https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/> .
@prefix case-investigation: <https://ontology.caseontology.org/case/investigation/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .


